The mac MenuItem handles the tooltip by the native NSMenuItem class by setting the tooltip string only. The gtk menu uses a native call, like the mac code, to set the tooltip.

Both of them do not use a special swt widget for the tooltip handling like the code for win32.

Beside of looking into the code, im not able to run the repro of the bug under gtk/mac to verify this analysis.
